description:
The JaCoCo minimum coverage threshold was temporarily set to 0% during project bootstrap because there's no production code to test yet. Once there's actual production code with tests, restore the threshold to 0.50 in build.gradle.kts:

```kotlin
tasks.jacocoTestCoverageVerification {
    violationRules {
        rule {
            limit {
                minimum = "0.50".toBigDecimal()  // Restore this from 0.00
            }
        }
    }
}
```

Create Employment API endpoints:
- GET /api/v1/persons/{personId}/employments
- GET /api/v1/employments/{id}
- POST /api/v1/persons/{personId}/employments
- PUT /api/v1/employments/{id}
- DELETE /api/v1/employments/{id}

Create Income API endpoints:
- GET /api/v1/employments/{employmentId}/incomes
- POST /api/v1/employments/{employmentId}/incomes
- PUT /api/v1/incomes/{id}
- DELETE /api/v1/incomes/{id}
